    "body": "@fubuloubu I'm starting to look into this one. One note for now, this guy also compiles:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# Compiles!\r\n@public\r\n@constant\r\ndef who(_arg: bytes[100]) -> int128:\r\n    return convert(slice(_arg, start=20, len=32), int128)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSeems like we may want to re-name this issue to be more specific to converting from `bytes` to `int128`, though perhaps we do want to also add converting from `bytes` to `address`? Though perhaps not converting from `bytes` to `decimal` as converting from `bytes32` to `decimal` is also not currently supported. Thoughts?",
