    "body": "Anything to decimal is interesting... I would prefer that all basic types (those that take up 32 bytes) be directly convertible to one another easily. But obviously certain transformations are problematic.\r\n\r\nFor example, converting uint256 to decimal. Does it... clamp at INT128_MAX? Naively convert the value, ignoring higher bits? Multiply by the 10 decimal places?\r\n\r\nNeeds to be well documented. We should probably have a pow-wow about this... @jakerockland can you create a table in the docs of what happens when you convert each type to another. Try to think through what scenarios would be problematic and how we could resolve them. Then we can all approve that as a VIP and make sure they get implemented as stated in the docs. Does that sound okay?\r\n\r\nTurning into a bit more of headache than anticipated!",
